beer_description: American style Amber whose color is produced by using caramel and victory malts. This caramel sweetness is balanced by a medium hop presence resulting in a medium bodied and hopped beer.
A traditional German Hefeweizen that boasts a fruity banana and clove taste. Using unique weiss yeast, after fermentation this beer is served unfiltered and with a fresh lemon wedge.
A light beer with a distinctive crisp flavor and floral overtones. Only Wisconsin Clover honey is used to produce this refreshing American style lager.

Rich, dark, robust. A cross between Dry Irish Stout and an English oatmeal stout. Caramel and roasted barley evoke complex chocolate and coffee flavors. A tasty twist on the National Drink of Ireland!

Classic nut brown ale. Originating in northeast England, this ale is more malty and toasty than the typical bitter Pale Ale of Britian. Its deep amber color and rich, full body make for a pleasing pint.

A smooth, potent brew. The Underground is highly hopped, using a process developed by the British Empire to preserve ales being shipped around Africa to its troops in India. Distinct "noble" style hops of England make this a true India Pale Ale. Higher than average alcohol content.

Unfiltered, Alpine-style wheat beer. Century-old yeast strains from Werhenstephan, Germany combine with other barley and wheat malts to produce this Bavarian "hefe-wiezen." Sample its distinctive banana and clove flavors.

Stout Brothers flagship ale. This cream ale embodies Yankee ingenuity - a unique combination of German-inspired pre-prohibition lagers and early American premium lagers. New World ingredients and revolutionary brewing techniques create a lighter, easy-drinking ale.

Clean, crisp, well-balanced. This authentic Bohemian lager uses only the finest imported Czech Republic yeast and hops. It ferments in our tanks longer (and colder) than our other beers. Euro-pils at its best!
A monster stout with a warming smooth malty finish and hints of roasted coffee and chocolate.

If you are a ?hophead,? this one?s for YOU! It?s fat, chewy and resiny and pungent. Pour into a wide-mouthed glass and get ready to RIP! 8.0% alcohol by volume.

A rich refreshing English pub style ale. The combination of brown and caramel malts give this ale body and its distinctive color. Moderately hopped for aroma and flavor. Named in honor of Jasper, an iron ore mineral found in this region.
An American Style ale named in honor of the iron rich, red colored earth found locally. The use of Northern Brewer and Cascade hops gives this ale an assertive hop bitterness, flavor and aroma.
An American style amber ale with medium maltiness. Northern Brewer and Willamette hops offer a mild hop bitterness, aroma and flavor.
An American pale ale. Medium bodied, slightly malty and aggressively hopped with Centennial and dry hopped with Cascade, clean and crisp. Our strongest ale.

This American-style ale has been one of our most popular; appealing to regional tastes for a medium-bodied beer with full ale taste and delicate hops flavor.

Like the old porters of Ireland, our porter is super-rich and velvety. It is deep brown in color, with richly roasted and chocolate-y flavors. Like all Marin Brewing Company Ales, this contains no preservatives and is not heat-pasteurized. 6.0% alcohol by volume.

This style was originally developed to be hard and bitter enough to withstand the travel and storage required to reach the torrid climate in India. When the soldiers returned home they found themselves so accustomed to its bold character, they requested it as a regular pub offering. 6.8-7% alcohol by volume.

Our amber-colored ales has a rich malty flavor, a smooth and a hoppy aroma and finish. It is brewed with a large amount of Crystal Malts which are roasted longer to add flavor and color in this ale. Named in recognition and memory of Sonoma?s New Albion Brewing Company, which opened in 1976 and was the first commercial micro-brewery since Prohibition. 5.0% alcohol by volume.

Since its release in 1995, Asahi Kuronama has become Japan?s favorite dark beer with its rich aroma and subtle sweetness. It is made from three types of dark roasted malt that each gives a different characteristic flavor according to how it is roasted and toasted. ?Dark malt? produces the distinct fragrance of dark beer. ?Crystal malt?imparts a delicate sweetness, and ?Munich malt? adds a fullness of taste. beer_description: A dark lager with a medium body. Brewed in the tradition of a Munich Dark Lager.

A ?light?, brown abbey ale with a deep colour with red reflections, chocolate, coffee and liquorice aromas and a touch of aniseed and white fruit notes. The first sip is full-flavoured, with a hint of acidity which heightens the roasted notes provided by the special malts. Malted flavours are prominent on the palate. The finish is particularly long, mainly acidic with a hint of sourness and a faint bitter aftertaste. Served cold, the spicy aromas will come to the fore, whereas when served at cellar temperature they give way to toasted, biscuit notes. Worth rediscovering again and again.
Golden clear colour, head dissipates fast. Taste is a bit acidic and fizzy.

Sunburn is a blonde ale with a light caramel body and subtle, refreshing hop aroma. This brew uses Citra hops, a new hop variety that only a few breweries have access to. This unique hop helps create a balanced and flavorful beer with little bitterness. Sunburn is one of four seasonal brews that Widmer Brothers will release this year, providing variety that highlights the tastes of each season. Beginning in 1986, Kurt and Rob were the first U.S. brewers to release a year round four beer seasonal lineup.
